abstract:
Part of the Vicmap Crown Land Tenure (Basic) dataset series.  This dataset is a decoded version of Vicmap Crown Land Tenure.  The model has been designed with simplicity of use in mind.  Attributes have been populated with values from the aspatial tables normally supplied with Vicmap Crown Land Tenure. 

Vicmap Crown Land Tenure is a statewide dataset series that plays a key role in the management of Victoria

s Crown land.  It was created (June 2003 - Feb 2004) from migrating LCMP layers into the Vicmap structure.

The dataset provides information about the Private use of Crown land Parcels and Crown Roads.  It contains a number of Tenure types including:
- (A) Agricultural including Unused Road licences, Water Frontage licences and Grazing licences,
- (L) Lease including Commercial type leases,
- (G) General Licences including miscellaneous community use licences, permits & consents
- (P) Pipe including Water supply pipelines,
- (RM) Reserve including land gazetted as a Reserve in Government Gazettes,
- Tenure Identifiers, Tenure type identifiers and Tenure code identifiers.
- Unique feature identifiers, date stamps and data quality information.
- Cross reference to Vicmap Property.

The database is continually maintained, obtaining maintenance from authoritative sources within State Government.

Part of the Vicmap Admin dataset series.  This layer contains polygon features delineating the current Fire Rescue Victoria District Boundaries.
 
 Polygon features delineating FRV's ten administrative districts. FRV Districts are a sub-group of FRV Regions.

 This data is current as of 1 Dec 2021.
